  <brief_title>A Research Study to Assess the Mechanism By Which Glucovance, Metformin, and Glyburide Work To Control Glucose Levels In Patients With Type 2 Diabetes</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Bristol-Myers Squibb</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Bristol-Myers Squibb</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this clinical research study is to support earlier observations that
      Glucovance controls glucose levels after a mean, and improves overall glucose control better
      than metformin or glyburide therapy alone in adults with type 2 diabetes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
